<div id="review_2935972568" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2935972568" />
    <a title="Trish" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3461034-trish"><img alt="Trish" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588663568p2/3461034.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2935972568?book_show_action=true">Aug 31, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Trish" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Trish" href="/user/show/3461034-trish">Trish</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780734415868" href="/book/show/23399671-the-arrival">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Trish by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/36890366-sud666">Sud666</a>
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2935972568" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2980577850405962079">I found this after a friend recommended it to me. <br/><br/>It‘s the story of a man leaving his country (and family) behind as there are monsters there. He embarks on a journey across the ocean, landing in a fantasy-version of NYC. There, he has to find his bearings, meets all kinds of people, manages to find work to ultimately send money back home that will bring his wife and daughter to him.<br/><br/>What makes this story special is that it is told in graphics only. The entire book only shows pictures, no text - </span>
  <span id="freeText2980577850405962079" style="display:none">I found this after a friend recommended it to me. <br><br>It‘s the story of a man leaving his country (and family) behind as there are monsters there. He embarks on a journey across the ocean, landing in a fantasy-version of NYC. There, he has to find his bearings, meets all kinds of people, manages to find work to ultimately send money back home that will bring his wife and daughter to him.<br><br>What makes this story special is that it is told in graphics only. The entire book only shows pictures, no text - but the illustrations (graphites) are gorgeous! They are all in sepia, sometimes darker, sometimes brighter, showing in incredible detail how strange yet wonderful this distant new land is.<br>We have fantasy creatures living side-by-side with the humans, the evil forces of oppression and war depicted as dragons and giant monsters.<br><br>The reader thus learns of the desperation of immigrants, of their alienation at simple things like food they‘ve never seen before, of the difficulty due to them not speaking the language at first - but the reader also learns of perseverance, hope and the immigrants working hard to make a new life.<br><br>A remarkable story that emphazises a very important topic - no, it‘s not timely as immigration is a very old subject, only being treated as if it was a new problem. As usual, both sides have to be looked at in order to obtain an informed opinion and most countries have benfitted from immigration workers throughout history (we‘re talking about the kind of immigrants that are grateful for a new chance, that want to learn the language and contribute in their new home).<br><br>Personally, more than the topic itself, I‘m still in awe of the book‘s design and Shaun Tan‘s illustrations that tell the story vividly without any words - no wonder this book won several awards.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1567253797i/28079384.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="2980577850405962079" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


