        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16297867-tisha?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1782560552" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16339915935274490038">OH MY GOD!!!!!! This is one of the best books I have ever read! Can I have some more stars to put?! <br/><br/>‘The Arrival’ is a book without words, a silent book! It has pictures, only pictures and they are mesmerizing! The writer and illustrator, Shaun Tan has done an amazing job. Hats off! His way of conveying emotions of the story to the reader only using pictures is totally out of the world! <br/><br/>It is a story of a man who leaves his country to find a better place for his family and ends up in a new place</span>
  <span id="freeText16339915935274490038" style="display:none">OH MY GOD!!!!!! This is one of the best books I have ever read! Can I have some more stars to put?! <br /><br />‘The Arrival’ is a book without words, a silent book! It has pictures, only pictures and they are mesmerizing! The writer and illustrator, Shaun Tan has done an amazing job. Hats off! His way of conveying emotions of the story to the reader only using pictures is totally out of the world! <br /><br />It is a story of a man who leaves his country to find a better place for his family and ends up in a new place where things are pretty weird! But gradually he gets used to these peculiar things and leads his life like a normal citizen of the town. <br />Basically it’s a story of immigrant people who face tons of problems in a new country. <br /><br />The departure of the man leaving his family behind was heartbreaking. But the ending just melted my heart! I wanted few more pages of it! Such a beautiful book. <br /><br />I have read the pdf version for now. But someday I’ll definitely collect a copy of it. &lt;3 <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16339915935274490038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

